pullRequest.body:
This is ported from the Mathlib 3 branch [`von_neumann_v2`](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib3/blob/5b3c1d3d66838f426b44cae25b615f26438c8acb/src/set_theory/zfc/ordinal.lean). This is meant as a small, initial PR to iron out any kinks (with the definition, notation, auto-ported lemmas, etc.) before fully developing the file.

Of particular note is the quite bare-bones definition of an ordinal. Surprisingly, our weakened transitivity assumption is equivalent to the much stronger claim that ordinals are well-ordered under `‚àà`; see #17001 for a proof.

I actually learned this definition as the normal one (an ordinal is a transitive set of transitive sets). Either that or a transitive set linearly ordered by epsilon, but I haven't heard of the definition of a transitive set on which epsilon is a transitive relation. No need to change anything, I'm just interested in the cultural differences.

Thanks! üöÄ

maintainer merge
I don't think we should deprecate these until the replacement exists (hopefully this should be soon anyway?)
These changes really aren't necessary! Both the old and new are valid style (I personally prefer the old version, but it's a matter of taste)

Doesn't `x.IsTransitive` automatically give that `b ‚àà c` together with `c ‚àà x` imply `b ‚àà x`? If so, I'm not sure I'd phrase this as "written in an even weaker form". Perhaps "The transitivity condition can be written without assuming `a ‚àà x` and `b ‚àà x`, and `isOrdinal_iff_isTrans` shows it is equivalent to the usual one." What do you think?
I like that phrasing better.
Hmm, I'm not entirely convinced this one and the one below should be lemmas since they're just combinations of `isTransitive` and lemmas about transitive sets. `mem_trans'` is fine though

There's a bunch of lemmas about `‚àà` and `‚äÜ` we can state on ordinals that aren't true for general transitive sets, such as
```lean 4
variable {x y z : ZFSet} 

example : IsOrdinal x ‚Üí IsOrdinal y ‚Üí x ‚äÜ y ‚Üí y ‚àà z ‚Üí x ‚àà z := sorry
example : IsOrdinal x ‚Üí IsOrdinal y ‚Üí x ‚äÜ y ‚à® y ‚äÜ x := sorry
example : IsOrdinal x ‚Üí IsOrdinal y ‚Üí x ‚àà y ‚à® x = y ‚à® y ‚àà x := sorry
```
I think it's convenient to have these small wrappers over `IsTransitive` - that way you don't have to stop and think whether a theorem holds for all transitive sets or is exclusive to ordinals.
Okay, fair enough
